title.narrative: SRH for Adolescents and Youth in Burundi

description.narrative: Cordaid will implement this program in consortium with CARE, Rutgers and UNFPA and will work with the education and health sectors and communities. We pay attention to good national and decentralized coordination and meaningful youth participation. We will provide SRH education and iinformation to in- and out-of-school youth, more youth-friendly SRH services and foster an enabling environment

The final beneficiaries of the program are young people aged 10-24 both in-school and out-of-school. Young people represent about 3.3 million persons (World Bank total population data 2013). We expect to reach about one third of them or 1.1m. Intermediate beneficiaries will be e.g. teachers, health service providers, youth- and Family and Communiyy Development Centers, peer educators, parents, community leaders, staff of national and local institutions. See project plan for more details.

The overall object is to empower adolescents and youth in Burundi so that they enjoy good sexual and reproductive health (SRH). Specifically: 1) In-school and out-of-school adolescents and youth have access to quality, youth-friendly SRH information, adopt favourable attitutdes and are able to make their own choice and practice responsibly. 2) Adolescents and youth have access to quality SRH services including family planning 3) key community actors protect and promote adolescent SRH 4) a strong coordination between partners and stakeholders in ASRH exists at the local and national level
